
User
 └── StudyPlan
       └── AI_Plan_Versions
             └── AI_Topic_Plans
                   └── Study_Sessions
                         └── Session_Tasks
                               └── User_Feedback


Core Tables
    1.  users
    2.  study_plans
    3.  ai_plan_versions
    4.  ai_topic_plans
    5.  study_sessions
    6.  session_tasks
    7.  user_feedback


-------------------------------------------------


1. Users (Who the learner is)
      id (PK)
      name
      email (unique)
      learning_pace           -- slow | medium | fast
      preferred_language
      created_at

->  Stable table
->  No AI dependency

-------------------------------------------------


2. study_plans (User intent & constraints (NO syllabus))
      id (PK)
      user_id (FK → users.id)
      subject                 -- e.g. "DSA"
      goal_type               -- clarity | exam | revision
      total_days
      daily_minutes
      start_date
      status                  -- active | completed | paused
      created_at

->  One user can have many study plans
->  This table NEVER changes when AI replans

-------------------------------------------------


3. ai_plan_versions (Version control for AI decisions)
      id (PK)
      study_plan_id (FK → study_plans.id)
      version_number
      trigger_reason           -- initial | missed_days | low_performance | user_request
      ai_model                 -- gemini-1.5, etc.
      is_active
      created_at


->  Only one active version per study_plan
->  Old versions kept for history & analytics

-------------------------------------------------


4. ai_topic_plans (AI-generated HIGH-LEVEL topics)
      id (PK)
      plan_version_id (FK → ai_plan_versions.id)
      topic_title              -- "Arrays & Basics"
      allocated_minutes
      sequence_order
      ai_reasoning JSON        -- why this topic, why this time

->  Generated dynamically
->  No predefined topics anywhere
->  This is the AI syllabus

-------------------------------------------------


5. study_sessions (One row = one study day)
      id (PK)
      plan_version_id (FK → ai_plan_versions.id)
      topic_plan_id (FK → ai_topic_plans.id)
      day_number               -- 1 to N
      available_minutes        -- Time user SHOULD EXPAND on Neurolearn
      actual_minutes_spent     -- Time user SPENDED on Neurolearn 
      session_status           -- pending | completed | skipped

->  Ensures daily discipline
->  Makes missed-day handling easy
->  By Compaering available_minutes and actual_minutes_spent
        Overload Detection
        Underutilization Detection
        Trend (Across Days)

-------------------------------------------------


6. session_tasks (AI-generated MICRO-LEARNING units)
      id (PK)
      study_session_id (FK → study_sessions.id)
      task_title
      task_type                -- concept | example | practice | revision
      estimated_minutes
      content JSON              -- explanation, examples, questions
      task_order
      completion_status

->  This is what the student actually studies
->  Generated based on available_minutes

-------------------------------------------------


7. user_feedback (Controls adaptiveness)
      id (PK)
      session_task_id (FK → session_tasks.id)
      understanding_level       -- clear | partial | not_clear
      time_spent_minutes
      user_note
      created_at

->  AI reads this before generating next session
->  Core to NeuroLearn’s “slow learner” promise







